Policy debating on higher level

The one-size-fit all rule book for structuring policies
will not take us very much further.

Today we will try to together generalize the knowledge behind
policies and apply them to discussions from less standard settings.

Warm-up:
- A problem requiring a policy - complex solution is shared.
- We develop a structure of a proper policy together
- One person tries to propose a policy conforming to the said format
- Then one person tries to find holes in the policy - question it soundness

Motions for warm-up:

With the Christianity's popularity declining among young people,
This house believes a new alternative religion should be proposed that
would help it's believers to navigate the world

This house believes that decline of birth rates should be address with a governmental policy.

Main debate motion :

In face of recent developments in the IT industry - programmers writing less code
and taking more responsibilities of product owners, This house as
the University Senate has decided to merge the course for IT and Management students
 into one and write it's program from scratch.

 We will together develop a structure of the format, then assigned teams would come up with
 two policies conforming to the format.

